COMMITTEE AMENDMENT

COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 265, L.D. 582
1 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
2 number to read consecutively.
3 SUMMARY
44 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, does the following.
5 1. It strikes the provision in the bill that prohibits a health insurance carrier from
6 imposing cost-sharing for coverage for blood testing for perfluoroalkyl and polyfluoroalkyl
7 substances.
8 2. It strikes the unallocated language section in the bill stating the Legislature's finding
9 that the coverage required in the bill is not an expansion of the State's essential health
10 benefits.
11 3. It changes the application date for the coverage requirement from January 1, 2026
12 to January 1, 2027.
13 4. It adds language exempting the bill from review and evaluation by the Department
14 of Professional and Financial Regulation, Bureau of Insurance.
15 5. It adds an appropriations and allocations section.
